comment.body:
@baentsch Following up on this after looking into patching in an updated name:

The `Falcon-* (PADDED)` name has already landed in PQClean. (I should probably have solicited feedback on that choice, earlier, mea culpa. :grimacing:) It should be an easy and quick fix to patch it (in `liboqs`) to `Falcon-*-padded` or `Falcon-*-PADDED` or what-have-you, in alg-param-variant order. However, switching to alg-variant-param will change the PQClean algorithm namespace from `PQCLEAN_FALCON512PADDED_*` to `PQCLEAN_FALCONPADDED512_*`. That's too big a change to fix easily with a patch, so it would require a PR upstream (one with a very large, albeit inconsequential diff) to change the name.

I'm OK with doing the work, but since we're aiming to cut a release candidate tomorrow, I thought I should check to see if it's worth potentially delaying that for naming conventions.

